And I don't have a flag that needs to be on there for certain versions of Ubuntu, which causes a security vulnerability.

00:41:23.820 --> 00:41:30.280
And then, you know, my post is popping up and a lot of people basically have security vulnerabilities in their SSH keys because it's something that I wrote.

00:41:30.280 --> 00:41:32.520
Like Matt told me to do it this way.

00:41:32.520 --> 00:41:33.820
Well, Matt was wrong this time.

