And I went back and I fixed it.

00:41:37.040 --> 00:41:39.080
But I mean, it was out there for a long time.

00:41:39.080 --> 00:41:40.580
So I think that's kind of the leap.

00:41:40.580 --> 00:41:43.860
You have to ask yourself, like, do I feel comfortable with what I'm putting out here?

00:41:43.860 --> 00:41:46.400
Because, you know, there's a lot more people who are reading that.

00:41:46.400 --> 00:41:47.160
They're following that.

00:41:47.160 --> 00:41:51.800
And just like we copy and paste off Stack Overflow, you don't, as a developer, you're just trying to get something done.

00:41:51.800 --> 00:41:54.060
You don't always do the work yourself.

00:41:54.060 --> 00:41:56.280
You just say, okay, this is a solution to a problem.

00:41:56.280 --> 00:41:59.980
I put this in regardless of whether there's an issue with it or not.

00:41:59.980 --> 00:42:03.440
So I think that's a big leap when you're in one of these roles.

00:42:03.760 --> 00:42:06.320
Yeah, kind of like what Matt was saying.

